A SANGOMA who is charged for sexual assault and rape has abandoned his bail application. The 71-year-old appeared in the Motherwell Magistrates Court on Wednesday, 27 January where he was set to apply for bail. The accused was arrested on 19 January. At the accused’s court previous court appearance on 21 January, he indicated he wanted to apply for bail. However, he withdrew the bail application after three fresh sexual assault cases were opened against him. Colonel Priscilla Naidu said “The traditional healer who appeared in the Motherwell Magistrates Court for sexual assault and rape has abandoned his bail application and is remanded in custody until 11 May. “It is alleged the accused lured boys and one girl, aged between 13 and 18 years old, on separate occasions or at the same time to his house in Mgwalana Street in Motherwell,” she said “He informed the victims that he will give them a belt that will protect them against evil spirits. When they went inside, he made them take off their clothes and caressed them with the belt. They further alleged that they became very disoriented and that’s when he sexually molested them. “One victim reported the incident to his parents. Since his arrest, three other cases have been opened against him. Two were for sexual assault and one charge was of compelled rape,” said Naidu.